                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47475",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=m%C3%B4shevds",
                        "name": "m\u00f4shevds",
                        "displayName": "M\u00f4she van der Sterre",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The reason this worked in 1.11.7 is because the route was ignored completely, and only the module\/controller\/action was checked.\r\n\r\nHowever, changing the handling of the null parameter (for the locale in your case) will fix this issue (but I'm not sure if that is the correct thing to do).\r\n\r\nLook at this patch on how to do that:\r\nhttp:\/\/pastie.org\/2203185",
